{"source_key":"sha256-784c2f10bfe4a26d66c37ad545f72f01","record_index":17635,"record_hash":"sha256:ef25db505c333e1ccacbd9c4e26706e3beea43e066a8fed23a8e74a41e2600cd","timestamp":"2026-05-10T07:10:56.744Z","kind":"message","source_event_kind":"codex:response_item:message","role":"assistant","text":"I think we’re still good, with one caveat: `Role` should stay a **small normalized conversation role**, not become a dumping ground for every provider event type.\n\nClaude actually makes the case *for* the enum a bit stronger: `UserMessage` and `AssistantMessage` are first-class concepts, and tool results flowing back as `UserMessage` is exactly the kind of nuance where a normalized role helps future readers/renderers.\n\nSo I’d keep:\n\n```rust\nUser\nDeveloper\nAssistant\nSystem\nTool\nOther(String)\n```\n\nAnd keep these boundaries:\n\n- `role` = speaker/message role when present or obvious\n- `event_kind` = provider/event shape like `system:init`, `assistant:message`, `response_item`\n- no attempt to force every record to have a role\n- no extra Claude-specific role variants unless we see actual transcript values\n\nThat feels pragmatic rather than bloated.","tool_name":null,"tool_input":null,"source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-10T07:10:56.744Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"message","role":"assistant","phase":"final_answer"}}}